title: For Sale:  Windham Weaponry AR 15 with ECHO Trigger
postcontent: For sale is a Windham Weaponry AR15 .223/5.56.  Includes installed Echo trigger system, 10" aluminum one-piece/free float rail from Midwest Industries, Troy low profile glass block, Magpul angled foregrip and Magpul Flip-up sights.  Rifle with trigger and magazines is $1,200.  Eotech and ammo not included in this price.  Echo trigger alone sells for $480.  This trigger gives you three settings.  Safe, Semi-Auto (semi-auto has nice trigger pull and reset) and "Echo" mode.  In Echo mode, the rifle fires once on trigger pull as normal but fires a second round on trigger release.  This gives you the ability quickly fire 2 shots and simulate full auto speed without using a bumpfire style stock.  You can Google search the trigger if you are interested in more information.  Very nice trigger system that is fun to shoot.  Military Arms Channel on Youtube also does a nice review of the trigger.Will sell the Eotech 512 for $340 with or without the rifle.Also have 1000 rounds of ammo in an ammo can that I will sell for $260.I would also consider trades for a nice Remington 700 .308 with a bull barrel +/- cash.

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory M1 Garand 1953 Marlin barrel
postcontent: This is an interesting Springfield Armory M1 Garand. The ser# is 4227415.,p> Marlin barrels were used on Springfield Armory M1 Garands between ser# 4,2xx,xxx and 4,3xx,xxx. Marlin made barrels for M1 Garands for WWII, but most of these were rejected. They also produced barrels after WWII.This is barrel is a blued WWII production barrel with the numbers and name on the top, the letter P on the side, and the flaming bomb on the bottom.The chamber is bright, so it has not been refinished.I believe this was one of the good ones.The throat/chamber measures out 2 of 10The muzzle measures 1.5 out of 3.The serial number dates this to 1953, and it may have been used late in the Korean war.
